{{see|Spirit}}
==English==

{{rank|early|saying|talk|450|spirit|sometimes|account|party}}

===Etymology===
{{L.}} '''[[spiritus]]''', ultimately meaning ''breath'', ''wind'' (cf. ''[[inspire]]'', ''[[respire]]'', ''[[transpire]]''), from '''[[spirare]]''', ''[[breathe]]''

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪrɪt|-ɪrɪt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[soul]] of a [[person]] or other living being
# A [[supernatural]] being, often but not exclusively without physical form; [[ghost]], [[fairy]], [[angel]]
# [[Enthusiasm]]
#: ''School '''spirit''' is at an all-time high''
# Manner or style
#: ''In the '''spirit''' of previous efforts, we have continued to use italics excessively''
# A volatile liquid, such as [[alcohol]]. The plural form [[spirits]] is a generic term for all alcoholic beverages.

